post_cb({"25394763": {"ParentId": "25394665", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>Yes, the code is valid and value initializes each element of the array. </p>\n<p>For standard references, refer to <em>\u00a75.3.4/17 [expr.new]</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_25394665_25394763_0\">A new-expression that creates an object of type T initializes that object as follows:<br/>\n  \u2014 <code>...</code><br/>\n  \u2014 Otherwise, the new-initializer is interpreted according to the initialization rules of 8.5 for direct-initialization.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>and then <em>\u00a78.5/7 [dcl.init]</em></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_25394665_25394763_1\">To value-initialize an object of type T means:<br/>\n  \u2014 <code>...</code><br/>\n  \u2014 if T is an array type, then each element is value-initialized;<br/>\n  \u2014 otherwise, the object is zero-initialized.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The last bullet applies to each array element in this case.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "241631", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "25394763", "Score": "2", "CreationDate": "2014-08-19T23:52:09.533", "LastActivityDate": "2014-08-19T23:52:09.533"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_25394665_25394763_0": {"section_id": 6098, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}, "so_25394665_25394763_1": {"section_id": 3287, "quality": 1.0, "length": 13}}, "n3337": {"so_25394665_25394763_0": {"section_id": 5864, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}, "so_25394665_25394763_1": {"section_id": 3157, "quality": 1.0, "length": 13}}, "n4659": {"so_25394665_25394763_0": {"section_id": 7595, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}, "so_25394665_25394763_1": {"section_id": 4049, "quality": 0.9230769230769231, "length": 12}}}, "25394665": {"CommentCount": "1", "AcceptedAnswerId": "25394763", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "2296458", "CreationDate": "2014-08-19T23:39:28.223", "LastActivityDate": "2014-08-19T23:52:09.533", "LastEditDate": "2014-08-19T23:40:00.237", "ViewCount": "488", "FavoriteCount": "0", "Title": "Can a C++11 initializer-list be used with a dynamic array?", "Id": "25394665", "Score": "1", "Body": "<p>Is this valid C++ to initialize a dynamic array of pointers to <code>nullptr</code>?</p>\n<pre><code>int x = 10;\nint** p = new int*[ x ]{ };\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><initializer-list>", "OwnerUserId": "242321", "AnswerCount": "1"}});